news.title: Sweden: Skanska operating profit grew 189% in Oct-Dec 2024
news.para: The Nordic region's biggest builder said its operating profit grew 189% on a currency adjusted basis to 2.75 billion Swedish crowns ($252.2 million) in the October-December quarter.

news.title: Average rate on a 30-year mortgage in USA falls to 6.89%
news.para: The average rate fell to 6.89% from 6.95% last week, mortgage buyer Freddie Mac said Thursday. A year ago, it averaged 6.64%.

news.title: TARC posts Rs 29 crore net loss in Q3 FY25
news.para: Total income increased marginally to Rs 11.21 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal year from Rs 10.51 crore in the corresponding period of the preceding year, according to a regulatory filing on Thursday.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh cabinet approves development authority for Shahjahanpur
news.para: Part of the Bareli administrative division, a survey will be conducted in the 49 revenue villages in Shahjahanpur, which would fall under the jurisdiction of the authority.

news.title: House prices in UK jump by 0.7% in January 2025: Halifax
news.para: House prices climbed by 0.7% in monthly terms last month after falling by 0.2% in December, Halifax said, above a 0.2% increase forecast by economists in a Reuters poll.

news.title: Mumbai: Soon, unmetered properties must pay water, sewage taxes
news.para: According to the Maharashtra govt decision of Feb 2, 2022, residential properties under 500 square feet were exempt from water and sewerage taxes.

news.title: Noida: Developers want to avail rehabilitation policy for five stalled projects
news.para: If YEIDA agrees, officials said, the developers in return will file applications to withdraw cases pending in the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) and in other courts.

news.title: Guntur civic body to focus on bringing more households into tax bracket
news.para: The commissioner found that many residential and commercial buildings were left without imposing property taxes during his field visit and constituted special teams to immediately complete the tax assessment process.

news.title: Titan America raises $384 million in US IPO
news.para: Titan America sold 9 million shares, together with 15 million shares its Belgium-based parent company Titan Cement International offered at $16 apiece. The company had marketed to list its shares in a range of $15-$18 apiece.

news.title: Lucknow development body to organise camp to address map related issues
news.para: The camp aims to process pending map approvals, new map applications, and No Objection Certificates (NOCs) promptly.

news.title: Raymond to jointly develop residential project in Mahim West, Mumbai
news.para: This project is estimated to have a revenue potential of approximately Rs 1,800 crore. This project will be the second residential project that the company will be developing in Mahim West, Mumbai.

news.title: Akzo Nobel India's net profit declines 4.57% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Akzo Nobel India's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,056.50 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 1.48 per cent from Rs 1,041.10 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Hyderabad: After illegal villa razed by HYDRAA, owner files case against builder for cheating
news.para: Based on a Look Out Circular (LOC) issued by Cyberabad police, she was nabbed at the Rajiv Gandhi International Airport (RGIA) on Jan 30 and later arrested by Dundigal police.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers signs 22 acres joint development project in Pune
news.para: The project, spread over 22 acres, with the total potential saleable area of about 5 million sq ft, has an expected gross developable value (GDV) of Rs. 4,000 crore.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: NGT halts real estate project in Ghatikia for not meeting green norms
news.para: According to sources, the realtor took building plan approval from Bhubaneswar Development Authority (BDA) for constructing 12 towers in a residential project. The builder completed construction of eight towers.

news.title: RBI's repo rate cut to boost real estate sector: Experts
news.para: Real estate experts feel this rate cut will have a positive impact on the overall sector, making home loans more affordable and increasing demand for housing.

news.title: MHADA invites bids to allot 450 flats under EWS quota in Nashik
news.para: It is mandatory for builders or developers to reserve 20% of flats for EWS in residential projects coming up on or above 4,000 sq metres, according to the norms. This is applicable in cities with a population of over 10 lakh.

news.title: RBI cuts policy rate by 25 bps to 6.25%, first reduction in five years
news.para: The Monetary Policy Committee (MPC) unanimously decided to slash policy rate by 25 basis points to 6.25 per cent, said Sanjay Malhotra, Governor, RBI.

news.title: Maharashtra: Masking Aadhaar info in old property papers a challenge
news.para: Officials from the registration department said they were collaborating with the National Informatics Centre (NIC) to address the issue in over 3 crore documents already available on govt websites.

news.title: Approval delays hurt pre-sales bookings of top realty developers
news.para: Prestige, Puravankara, Godrej Properties, DLF, and Macrotech are among companies battling lengthy project approval timelines in key markets such as Mumbai, Pune, Bengaluru, Hyderabad, and Delhi-NCR.
